Lynn R. BRODRICK, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Kansas, v. David C. WHITE. No. 4505. United. States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Aug. 13, 1952. Eugene W. Davis, U. S. Atty., and V. J. Bowersock, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellant. W. D. Jochems, Wichita, Kan., for ap-pellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant. D.C., 104 F.Supp. 213.
